53
00:03:09,710 --> 00:03:10,750
Call her whatever you want.

54
00:03:10,750 --> 00:03:11,610
Call her wifey.

55
00:03:12,080 --> 00:03:12,750
Anything is fine.

56
00:03:12,750 --> 00:03:13,940
Anything.

57
00:03:16,630 --> 00:03:17,250
Wifey,

58
00:03:17,250 --> 00:03:19,150
I'm here to take you home!

59
00:03:20,190 --> 00:03:21,120
Who is it?

60
00:03:22,590 --> 00:03:23,079
Xiaobao.

61
00:03:23,079 --> 00:03:23,579
Xiaobao.

62
00:03:23,579 --> 00:03:24,680
I'm your brother-in-law.

63
00:03:24,680 --> 00:03:26,480
Brother-in-law, open the door!

64
00:03:27,210 --> 00:03:28,550
It's the groom.

65
00:03:29,030 --> 00:03:30,990
Listen up, Groom, hear me well,

66
00:03:31,060 --> 00:03:32,910
Say your hellos, or you’ll stay in your shell.

67
00:03:32,910 --> 00:03:34,940
If the red packets are way too light,

68
00:03:34,970 --> 00:03:37,430
The bride won't be leaving with you tonight!

69
00:03:37,800 --> 00:03:39,800
- Xiaobao, that is a good one.
- Yeah.

70
00:03:40,440 --> 00:03:42,210
Look at this kid.

71
00:03:42,400 --> 00:03:43,810
Are the red envelopes ready?

72
00:03:43,810 --> 00:03:45,740
Brother-in-law, here are the red envelopes.

73
00:03:45,740 --> 00:03:47,950
Here you go.

74
00:03:49,180 --> 00:03:49,980
Pick it up.

75
00:03:50,079 --> 00:03:50,940
Is that enough?

76
00:03:52,579 --> 00:03:54,000
This isn't even enough to share.

77
00:03:54,000 --> 00:03:55,300
Is that all?

78
00:03:55,410 --> 00:03:56,760
You're not sincere.

79
00:03:57,810 --> 00:03:58,410
Come on.

80
00:03:58,500 --> 00:03:59,460
Here's more.

81
00:03:59,460 --> 00:04:00,310
Give them a little at a time.

82
00:04:00,310 --> 00:04:01,850
- A little at a time.
- Okay.

83
00:04:02,150 --> 00:04:03,150
Here's more!

84
00:04:03,150 --> 00:04:03,980
There aren't many people left.

85
00:04:03,980 --> 00:04:04,960
All right, open the door.

86
00:04:04,960 --> 00:04:06,020
Bring them all here.

87
00:04:06,020 --> 00:04:07,810
This won't do.

88
00:04:07,870 --> 00:04:10,890
- Not enough.
- You have to pass Xiaobao's test first.

89
00:04:11,020 --> 00:04:12,020
Okay, no problem.

90
00:04:12,190 --> 00:04:13,830
Xiaobao, test them well.

91
00:04:14,190 --> 00:04:14,580
Okay.

92
00:04:14,720 --> 00:04:15,780
What test?

93
00:04:16,050 --> 00:04:17,149
You sing a song

94
00:04:17,180 --> 00:04:18,980
that Zhuang Zhuang used to sing.

95
00:04:19,200 --> 00:04:20,040
You gotta sing it.

96
00:04:20,040 --> 00:04:21,680
Sing? Sing what?

97
00:04:22,600 --> 00:04:23,520
Hear this one,

98
00:04:25,630 --> 00:04:28,300
I love Beijing Tian'anmen, Bei...

99
00:04:28,510 --> 00:04:29,930
Didn't you sing that?

100
00:04:30,000 --> 00:04:30,650
Yes.

101
00:04:30,950 --> 00:04:31,680
Ranran sang it.

102
00:04:31,680 --> 00:04:32,630
This is Ranran's song.

103
00:04:32,630 --> 00:04:34,130
- Zhuang Zhuang! - Zhuang Zhuang!

104
00:04:34,130 --> 00:04:36,420
- I'm a bit nervous. - [Ocean, My Hometown] is fine too.

105
00:04:36,420 --> 00:04:38,060
[Beat the Hand Drum and Sing].

106
00:04:38,060 --> 00:04:38,720
This works.

107
00:04:38,720 --> 00:04:40,330
The sea...

108
00:04:40,330 --> 00:04:41,310
No, beat the hand drum...

109
00:04:41,310 --> 00:04:43,470
Beat the hand drum and sing a song.

110
00:04:46,000 --> 00:04:48,340
Beat the hand drum and sing a song.

111
00:04:48,480 --> 00:04:49,750
Every

112
00:04:49,950 --> 00:04:51,390
bullet

113
00:04:51,450 --> 00:04:53,140
eliminates an enemy.

114
00:04:53,220 --> 00:04:55,210
We are all flying troops.

115
00:04:55,300 --> 00:04:57,900
Even if the mountains are high and waters deep.

116
00:05:12,270 --> 00:05:14,580
Beat the hand drum and sing a song.

117
00:05:14,620 --> 00:05:18,190
Riding a horse over the hillside.

118
00:05:18,510 --> 00:05:19,810
Open the door.

119
00:05:20,510 --> 00:05:21,920
How was the singing?

120
00:05:22,240 --> 00:05:24,030
You mixed up the songs.

121
00:05:24,390 --> 00:05:25,040
Xiaobao,

122
00:05:25,040 --> 00:05:26,840
let's say they passed this test.

123
00:05:27,180 --> 00:05:28,610
In such a hurry?

124
00:05:28,640 --> 00:05:29,260
Okay.

125
00:05:29,540 --> 00:05:30,640
Next question.

126
00:05:30,690 --> 00:05:33,060
What's the name of the movie brother Xu wrote?

127
00:05:33,060 --> 00:05:34,460
You can't get this wrong.

128
00:05:35,270 --> 00:05:36,590
[The Late Love].

129
00:05:36,960 --> 00:05:37,850
Ranran,

130
00:05:38,100 --> 00:05:38,680
well,

131
00:05:38,700 --> 00:05:40,560
