863
00:31:44,290 --> 00:31:44,720
Cheers.

864
00:31:44,720 --> 00:31:45,880
All right? Come on.

865
00:31:48,940 --> 00:31:50,620
Then let's wish ourselves

866
00:31:51,010 --> 00:31:53,620
even greater success.

867
00:31:53,740 --> 00:31:55,000
Even greater success.

868
00:31:59,960 --> 00:32:00,830
Mr. Jia, look,

869
00:32:00,860 --> 00:32:01,820
our down jackets

870
00:32:01,900 --> 00:32:02,760
have 90% down,

871
00:32:02,830 --> 00:32:04,030
pure white duck down.

872
00:32:04,180 --> 00:32:05,110
You can touch it.

873
00:32:05,110 --> 00:32:06,120
Feel the texture,

874
00:32:06,250 --> 00:32:07,380
and the resilience.

875
00:32:07,510 --> 00:32:08,470
I can guarantee

876
00:32:08,720 --> 00:32:09,920
that our down jackets

877
00:32:09,920 --> 00:32:11,650
will definitely not leak down.

878
00:32:12,610 --> 00:32:15,270
We've been selling down jackets for ten years.

879
00:32:16,010 --> 00:32:18,010
We can tell good quality at a glance.

880
00:32:19,740 --> 00:32:20,480
But,

881
00:32:21,550 --> 00:32:23,720
you know how the market is right now.

882
00:32:24,380 --> 00:32:26,830
You young people come out to make a living,

883
00:32:27,240 --> 00:32:28,840
and you have determination.

884
00:32:29,160 --> 00:32:29,650
But,

885
00:32:30,200 --> 00:32:31,740
don't blame us old geezers

886
00:32:31,740 --> 00:32:33,140
for being cold-blooded.

887
00:32:34,240 --> 00:32:35,680
We have to support our family.

888
00:32:35,680 --> 00:32:36,920
If I buy stock from you,

889
00:32:36,920 --> 00:32:37,750
and it doesn't sell,

890
00:32:37,750 --> 00:32:39,480
I won't be able to answer for it.

891
00:32:40,460 --> 00:32:41,920
I completely understand.

892
00:32:42,070 --> 00:32:43,040
How about this?

893
00:32:43,610 --> 00:32:45,270
I brought some samples today.

894
00:32:45,380 --> 00:32:47,250
I'll give them all to you

895
00:32:47,440 --> 00:32:48,220
for free.

896
00:32:48,700 --> 00:32:49,420
If they sell well,

897
00:32:49,420 --> 00:32:50,380
you can come back to me,

898
00:32:50,380 --> 00:32:52,420
and I'll give you the lowest price possible.

899
00:32:52,420 --> 00:32:52,900
Mr. Jia,

900
00:32:53,590 --> 00:32:54,680
I am very confident

901
00:32:54,830 --> 00:32:55,880
in our products.

902
00:32:59,720 --> 00:33:01,190
Then let's do this.

903
00:33:01,330 --> 00:33:03,130
Bring me another twenty pieces.

904
00:33:03,270 --> 00:33:04,370
I'll pay for them.

905
00:33:04,640 --> 00:33:05,070
And,

906
00:33:05,380 --> 00:33:06,200
since

907
00:33:06,270 --> 00:33:07,900
I know many distributors,

908
00:33:08,180 --> 00:33:09,910
I'll give them some samples too

909
00:33:10,180 --> 00:33:11,840
to help you open up the market.

910
00:33:12,200 --> 00:33:12,850
Then, Mr. Jia,

911
00:33:12,850 --> 00:33:14,700
about what we discussed before,

912
00:33:17,220 --> 00:33:17,940
no rebranding?

913
00:33:17,940 --> 00:33:18,690
Yes.

914
00:33:19,640 --> 00:33:20,220
About this,

915
00:33:20,220 --> 00:33:22,110
I'll definitely make it clear to them before.

916
00:33:22,110 --> 00:33:24,140
If they can accept it, we'll talk.

917
00:33:25,900 --> 00:33:26,500
Okay.

918
00:33:26,680 --> 00:33:27,720
Thank you, Mr. Jia.

919
00:33:27,720 --> 00:33:29,200
I'll go get the samples for you.

920
00:33:29,200 --> 00:33:30,310
Yes, hurry up.

921
00:33:30,380 --> 00:33:31,530
- Wait a moment.
- Do you need someone to carry it?

922
00:33:31,530 --> 00:33:32,990
No need, I can do it myself.

923
00:33:47,770 --> 00:33:48,850
Dinner time.

924
00:34:16,480 --> 00:34:17,420
Get up and eat.

925
00:34:20,260 --> 00:34:21,520
You must be exhausted.

926
00:34:24,070 --> 00:34:24,600
I'm fine.

927
00:34:25,340 --> 00:34:25,940
Let's eat.

928
00:34:28,520 --> 00:34:30,980
This food looks delicious.

929
00:34:33,969 --> 00:34:35,120
I'm really hungry.

930
00:34:37,210 --> 00:34:38,070
Eat slowly.

931
00:34:38,210 --> 00:34:39,139
It's delicious.

932
00:34:39,260 --> 00:34:40,940
But compared to you,

933
00:34:40,960 --> 00:34:42,090
it's not even close.

934
00:34:42,510 --> 00:34:44,370
I'll cook for you when we get back.

935
00:34:46,300 --> 00:34:47,590
Aren't you curious

936
00:34:47,590 --> 00:34:49,080
how our goods sold today?

937
00:34:49,380 --> 00:34:50,940
Let's finish eating first.

938
00:34:55,380 --> 00:34:56,179
Where is Meng?

939
00:34:56,870 --> 00:34:58,070
I let him go home.

940
00:34:58,370 --> 00:35:00,230
He's been running around all day.

941
00:35:01,590 --> 00:35:02,000
Yeah.

942
00:35:04,240 --> 00:35:05,650
Meng is quite hardworking.

943
00:35:05,650 --> 00:35:06,820
And he's very dedicated

944
00:35:06,820 --> 00:35:07,550
to our shop.

945
00:35:09,010 --> 00:35:10,030
He closed his own shop,

946
00:35:10,030 --> 00:35:11,340
but he didn't lose heart.

947
00:35:11,340 --> 00:35:13,100
He's still very driven.

948
00:35:14,340 --> 00:35:15,230
How about this?

949
00:35:17,230 --> 00:35:18,480
We can take his previous goods

950
00:35:18,480 --> 00:35:19,780
that he wants to clear out,

951
00:35:19,780 --> 00:35:20,610
sell them here,

952
00:35:20,610 --> 00:35:22,110
and give him all the money.

953
00:35:22,300 --> 00:35:23,050
Sure.

954
00:35:24,550 --> 00:35:25,610
He probably bought those goods

955
00:35:25,610 --> 00:35:27,090
with his own savings.

956
00:35:27,400 --> 00:35:28,900
It must be painful for him to be stuck with all this stock.

957
00:35:28,900 --> 00:35:29,780
Let's do it.

958
00:35:31,090 --> 00:35:31,610
Mr. Xu.

959
00:35:33,070 --> 00:35:33,670
Mr. Chen.

960
00:35:34,260 --> 00:35:35,280
You're still in the market so late?

961
00:35:35,280 --> 00:35:35,860
Yeah.

962
00:35:36,000 --> 00:35:37,000
Mr. Chen.

963
00:35:37,030 --> 00:35:37,670
Hello.

964
00:35:37,670 --> 00:35:38,150
Hello.

965
00:35:38,230 --> 00:35:39,420
I've heard so much about you.

966
00:35:39,420 --> 00:35:40,110
Come, sit.

967
00:35:40,110 --> 00:35:41,970
- Okay. - Let me get you some water.

968
00:35:42,590 --> 00:35:43,300
Having a meal?

969
00:35:43,300 --> 00:35:44,570
How about I get you some chopsticks

970
00:35:44,570 --> 00:35:45,260
so you can have a taste?

971
00:35:45,260 --> 00:35:46,390
I've already eaten.

972
00:35:46,780 --> 00:35:47,170
Here.

973
00:35:47,630 --> 00:35:48,420
Okay. Thank you.

974
00:35:48,420 --> 00:35:49,480
Let's talk while you eat.

975
00:35:49,480 --> 00:35:50,230
It's fine.

976
00:35:51,060 --> 00:35:53,390
All right. I'll get straight to the point.

977
00:35:55,690 --> 00:35:56,760
I mentioned this last time.

978
00:35:56,760 --> 00:35:58,690
The down jacket business is tough.

979
00:35:58,960 --> 00:35:59,690
My words might be harsh,

980
00:35:59,690 --> 00:36:00,750
please don't mind.

981
00:36:00,900 --> 00:36:01,500
It's okay.

982
00:36:01,610 --> 00:36:02,410
So I came today

983
00:36:02,500 --> 00:36:04,210
to help you.

984
00:36:05,030 --> 00:36:05,590
Go ahead.

985
00:36:07,010 --> 00:36:08,810
We all do business on Yabao Road.

986
00:36:08,920 --> 00:36:10,320
Friction is inevitable.

987
00:36:10,570 --> 00:36:12,030
But our general direction

988
00:36:12,170 --> 00:36:13,010
is the same.

989
00:36:13,550 --> 00:36:15,510
Only when the whole industry thrives,

990
00:36:15,510 --> 00:36:17,160
can we thrive. Right?

991
00:36:17,570 --> 00:36:18,000
Yes.

992
00:36:18,420 --> 00:36:18,860
Right.

993
00:36:19,380 --> 00:36:21,030
So, I want to

994
00:36:21,400 --> 00:36:24,000
give you some advice as an experienced person.

995
00:36:25,550 --> 00:36:25,980
I know

996
00:36:26,000 --> 00:36:27,910
you look down on OEM products.

997
00:36:28,920 --> 00:36:29,530
But I'm sorry to tell you,

998
00:36:29,530 --> 00:36:31,130
this is what the market needs.

999
00:36:31,130 --> 00:36:33,150
A little compromise

1000
00:36:33,480 --> 00:36:35,810
could keep several major plants running.

1001
00:36:35,840 --> 00:36:36,860
Just to prove a point,

1002
00:36:36,860 --> 00:36:38,460
running a business at a loss,

1003
00:36:38,860 --> 00:36:39,940
going hungry yourself,

1004
00:36:39,940 --> 00:36:41,540
and letting your men suffer.

1005
00:36:42,610 --> 00:36:44,610
That’s just not being responsible.

1006
00:36:46,130 --> 00:36:46,780
So,

1007
00:36:47,300 --> 00:36:48,840
I can give you

1008
00:36:48,840 --> 00:36:50,010
a little support.

1009
00:36:51,760 --> 00:36:53,150
I've seen your products.

1010
00:36:53,150 --> 00:36:54,610
The quality is excellent.

1011
00:36:54,820 --> 00:36:56,180
If they were in my hands,

1012
00:36:56,400 --> 00:36:57,280
I could easily pass them off

1013
00:36:57,280 --> 00:36:58,840
as European or American goods,

1014
00:36:58,840 --> 00:37:00,840
and sell them for the highest price.

1015
00:37:01,130 --> 00:37:01,710
So,

1016
00:37:02,000 --> 00:37:02,930
I hope from now on

1017
00:37:03,030 --> 00:37:04,900
you can process them for me.

1018
00:37:05,030 --> 00:37:06,210
You handle production,

1019
00:37:06,210 --> 00:37:07,610
and I handle sales.

1020
00:37:08,480 --> 00:37:09,030
Also, I have

1021
00:37:09,030 --> 00:37:10,510
what you need the most.

1022
00:37:11,780 --> 00:37:12,280
Money.

1023
00:37:12,960 --> 00:37:14,940
I can provide the upfront capital for you,

1024
00:37:14,940 --> 00:37:17,110
so you can at least get food on the table.

1025
00:37:17,110 --> 00:37:19,040
But it’s not just about getting by,

1026
00:37:19,210 --> 00:37:20,540
it’s about living well.

1027
00:37:20,980 --> 00:37:22,110
How does that sound?

1028
00:37:22,650 --> 00:37:24,030
Here's the thing, Mr. Chen.

1029
00:37:24,030 --> 00:37:24,690
It's not that we

1030
00:37:24,690 --> 00:37:26,150
look down on OEM products.

1031
00:37:26,170 --> 00:37:27,940
We just don't want to sell OEM products.

1032
00:37:27,940 --> 00:37:29,340
- It must be...
- Mr. Chen.

1033
00:37:31,110 --> 00:37:32,640
Our business philosophies

1034
00:37:33,380 --> 00:37:34,380
are fundamentally different.

1035
00:37:34,380 --> 00:37:35,870
There’s no common ground.

1036
00:37:36,280 --> 00:37:38,360
Let’s pass on this partnership.

1037
00:37:54,190 --> 00:37:54,920
Sorry to bother you.

1038
00:37:54,920 --> 00:37:55,680
Take care.

1039
00:37:56,780 --> 00:37:58,710
Look at him. It's quite cute.

1040
00:37:59,320 --> 00:38:00,850
What kind of person is that?

1041
00:38:01,570 --> 00:38:02,530
Doing the wrong thing himself

1042
00:38:02,530 --> 00:38:03,720
and wanting to drag us into it.

1043
00:38:03,720 --> 00:38:05,090
Honey, don't be angry.

1044
00:38:05,460 --> 00:38:06,860
Don't stoop to his level.

1045
00:38:07,630 --> 00:38:08,510
At least he said

1046
00:38:08,530 --> 00:38:09,770
our bear is cute.

1047
00:38:10,280 --> 00:38:11,360
Just eat.

1048
00:38:26,510 --> 00:38:28,170
Mr. Chen, you wanted to see me?

1049
00:38:30,210 --> 00:38:31,520
Got a new job,

1050
00:38:31,940 --> 00:38:33,600
so you ignore your old friend?

1051
00:38:34,110 --> 00:38:36,170
Mr. Chen, what are you talking about?

1052
00:38:36,940 --> 00:38:38,340
How are things over there?

1053
00:38:38,340 --> 00:38:39,070
Pretty good.

1054
00:38:42,130 --> 00:38:43,730
That couple is too stubborn.

1055
00:38:45,000 --> 00:38:45,590
Don't you agree

1056
00:38:45,590 --> 00:38:47,050
that this won't work out?

1057
00:38:50,800 --> 00:38:52,050
Mr. Xu and Zhuang

1058
00:38:52,460 --> 00:38:53,760
just lack experience.

1059
00:38:54,170 --> 00:38:55,500
They've had it too easy.

1060
00:38:55,730 --> 00:38:57,050
Maybe if they hit the wall sometime,

1061
00:38:57,050 --> 00:38:57,910
they'll learn.

1062
00:38:58,170 --> 00:38:58,940
You've been in this market

1063
00:38:58,940 --> 00:39:00,030
for so many years.

1064
00:39:01,280 --> 00:39:03,740
Have you ever seen anyone succeed like this?

1065
00:39:04,230 --> 00:39:05,360
How long can you last

1066
00:39:06,190 --> 00:39:07,450
on that meager salary?

1067
00:39:08,170 --> 00:39:09,780
Your own business went belly up,

1068
00:39:09,780 --> 00:39:11,380
and you’re drowning in debt.

1069
00:39:11,400 --> 00:39:13,130
If you want to stay in the shade,

1070
00:39:14,690 --> 00:39:16,650
you’d better find yourself a big tree.

1071
00:39:16,650 --> 00:39:17,500
Mr. Chen,

1072
00:39:17,900 --> 00:39:19,450
I really had no choice.

1073
00:39:19,590 --> 00:39:20,650
Why not?

1074
00:39:24,860 --> 00:39:25,720
You need money.

1075
00:39:27,880 --> 00:39:29,280
You could have come to me.

1076
00:39:29,710 --> 00:39:31,380
You know they're against me.

1077
00:39:32,090 --> 00:39:33,350
Instead of helping me,

1078
00:39:34,610 --> 00:39:36,410
you joined them to screw me over.

1079
00:39:37,050 --> 00:39:37,580
Mr. Chen,

1080
00:39:39,010 --> 00:39:40,710
who dares to go against you?

1081
00:39:40,900 --> 00:39:41,630
Doesn't the whole market

1082
00:39:41,630 --> 00:39:43,230
just pick up your leftovers?

1083
00:39:43,480 --> 00:39:44,810
Cut the crap.

1084
00:39:45,090 --> 00:39:45,750
Right here.

1085
00:39:47,380 --> 00:39:48,640
Partnering with them,

1086
00:39:49,780 --> 00:39:51,310
means standing against me.

1087
00:39:52,110 --> 00:39:53,240
To be my enemy,

1088
00:39:53,630 --> 00:39:55,160
you've heard what happens,

1089
00:39:57,010 --> 00:39:57,900
right?

1090
00:39:59,190 --> 00:40:01,370
Mr. Chen, what are you getting at?

1091
00:40:02,110 --> 00:40:03,110
This young couple

1092
00:40:04,460 --> 00:40:05,390
broke the rules.

1093
00:40:05,840 --> 00:40:07,500
But I didn't make these rules,

1094
00:40:08,630 --> 00:40:10,110
Yabao Road did.

1095
00:40:11,500 --> 00:40:13,560
The entire foreign trade market did.

1096
00:40:13,880 --> 00:40:15,680
I’m just representing our peers

1097
00:40:15,880 --> 00:40:17,740
to protect our common interests.

1098
00:40:17,980 --> 00:40:18,550
Right?

1099
00:40:21,260 --> 00:40:21,860
So,

1100
00:40:22,980 --> 00:40:24,380
I hope you stick with them

1101
00:40:25,210 --> 00:40:26,010
and work hard.

1102
00:40:27,270 --> 00:40:29,270
- Mr. Chen, don’t...
- Let me finish.

1103
00:40:29,630 --> 00:40:30,800
Work hard with them

1104
00:40:32,150 --> 00:40:33,280
and win their trust.

1105
00:40:34,320 --> 00:40:35,720
I'll find an opportunity

1106
00:40:36,030 --> 00:40:36,890
to devour them.

1107
00:40:37,490 --> 00:40:40,230
Bears, wolves, whatever,

1108
00:40:40,940 --> 00:40:42,050
they'll all be yours.

1109
00:40:42,050 --> 00:40:42,630
Mine?

1110
00:40:42,650 --> 00:40:43,150
Yours.

1111
00:40:59,420 --> 00:41:00,190
Mr. Chen.

1112
00:41:01,530 --> 00:41:02,090
So,

1113
00:41:02,460 --> 00:41:04,000
how long will this take?

1114
00:41:04,750 --> 00:41:05,400
Mr. Xu,

1115
00:41:05,670 --> 00:41:07,060
That Xu Shengli...

1116
00:41:07,190 --> 00:41:08,860
He’s actually a very meticulous man.

1117
00:41:08,860 --> 00:41:10,480
I'm afraid I'll be exposed if it takes too long.

1118
00:41:10,480 --> 00:41:11,810
Don't be in such a hurry.

1119
00:41:13,550 --> 00:41:15,940
Have you ever seen someone harvesting apples?

1120
00:41:15,940 --> 00:41:17,200
When the fruit is ripe,

1121
00:41:17,510 --> 00:41:19,230
one single strike with the pole,

1122
00:41:19,230 --> 00:41:20,760
saves both time and effort.

1123
00:41:21,000 --> 00:41:22,400
Don't ask any questions.

1124
00:41:23,110 --> 00:41:24,510
Just remember one thing,

1125
00:41:25,340 --> 00:41:26,740
Stick with me to get rich,

1126
00:41:28,030 --> 00:41:29,830
and you will prosper all the way.

1127
00:41:40,930 --> 00:41:42,770
The chairman only told me half of it.

1128
00:41:42,770 --> 00:41:44,330
Is he unwilling to help me?

1129
00:41:44,710 --> 00:41:45,840
Master Cao.

1130
00:41:46,150 --> 00:41:46,880
There are many things

1131
00:41:46,880 --> 00:41:48,360
that you still haven't figured out.

1132
00:41:48,360 --> 00:41:49,110
Well,

1133
00:41:49,130 --> 00:41:50,860
I have you to back me up, don't I?

1134
00:41:50,860 --> 00:41:52,600
Why don't you just tell me directly

1135
00:41:52,600 --> 00:41:54,250
what I should do?

1136
00:41:54,400 --> 00:41:55,320
The chairman promised

1137
00:41:55,320 --> 00:41:56,640
to do you a small favor.

1138
00:41:56,840 --> 00:41:57,800
And right away you expect him

1139
00:41:57,800 --> 00:41:59,200
to guide your every move?

1140
00:41:59,210 --> 00:42:00,550
Didn't I tell you?

1141
00:42:00,570 --> 00:42:01,530
The chairman's guidance

1142
00:42:01,530 --> 00:42:02,960
needs to be won at an auction.

1143
00:42:02,960 --> 00:42:05,160
Do you know how much that auction costs?

1144
00:42:05,900 --> 00:42:07,430
What the chairman told you,

1145
00:42:07,510 --> 00:42:09,110
have you completely forgotten?

1146
00:42:09,110 --> 00:42:10,250
Investments.

1147
00:42:10,480 --> 00:42:11,970
It's about high stakes.

1148
00:42:12,510 --> 00:42:13,340
No matter how small,

1149
00:42:13,340 --> 00:42:14,790
you must invest first

1150
00:42:14,820 --> 00:42:15,710
to get a return.

1151
00:42:17,260 --> 00:42:17,880
Right.

1152
00:42:18,360 --> 00:42:19,380
So now,

1153
00:42:19,460 --> 00:42:20,840
in which direction

1154
00:42:20,900 --> 00:42:22,160
should I invest first?

1155
00:42:23,440 --> 00:42:24,350
About this,

